<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1072" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1072">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3662.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at
                                    Chihuahua</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>.<lb/>[<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-19">undated</date>] (Received
                                April 19, 1912—3.30 p.m.)</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Two Americans have been imprisoned here since March 16 by the military
                            authorities without any excuse whatever; the detention has just come to
                            my notice. One of them is an honorably discharged sailor of our Navy.
                            Have demanded their immediate release.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>